1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:03,160
Next time you disappear without 
telling us anything, you’re out of the gang.

2
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:05,280
When he was gone, 
you were acting like a sad little puppy.

3
00:00:05,440 --> 00:00:06,360
Like hell I was.

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,520
What’s that light?

5
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:09,280
That’s us.

6
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:10,600
We’re about to head out to sea.

7
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:14,920
Did you leave a note on my desk?

8
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:18,720
Do you think I should 
study Sports Science like my senior?

9
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:19,560
Good idea.

10
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:20,880
That way, we can always stay together.

11
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:24,440
We’ve got the oranges, so we’re ready to go!

12
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:28,400
Orange.

13
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:30,360
Thanks for being my friend.

14
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,600
I won’t disappear again.

15
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:41,960
(Winter does not  only mean cool weather.)

16
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,320
Shake it harder.

17
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,920
Harder.

18
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:50,680
Why don’t you climb the tree 
and pick them, Ko Neung?

19
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,360
When will we get to eat oranges 
if we do this?

20
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:54,280
Come on. Keep shaking.

21
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:56,920
Come on. We almost got it.

22
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:59,480
(It’s also the symbol of our closer friendship.)

23
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:00,440
I arrived first.

24
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:01,160
Give me five baht.

25
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,720
(After we went on the boat trip,)

26
00:01:04,520 --> 00:01:07,560
(the five of us became inseparable.)

27
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:08,280
Ko.

28
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,560
August.

29
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,160
It tastes so good.

30
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,280
It’s ripe enough to eat.

31
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:34,000
(We share warmth and laughter 
while talking about things.) 

32
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,120
(It’s an unforgettable moment for me.)

33
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,920
(What happened on the boat that day?)

34
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,040
Ko Song.

35
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,360
Look there.

36
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,080
Give me the blanket too.

37
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:07,920
Stop pulling it.

38
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:08,520
Hey.

39
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:09,960
Stop it.

40
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:15,200
Give it to me.

41
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:31,000
Ko, wake up. The sun is up.

42
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,320
Ko.

43
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:36,480
Ko.

44
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:37,960
I want to sleep.

45
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,520
The school will open soon. 
You need to adjust your daily routine.

46
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:42,160
No.

47
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,400
Come on.

48
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,280
Okay, I’ll tell your friend to leave.

49
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,200
Who is it? Augar?

50
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:51,120
Ko Song.

51
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,520
Why did he come here so early?

52
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:56,760
How would I know?

53
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,160
When you hear your friend is here to see you, 
you get up right away.

54
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:00,920
But when it’s school day, 
you’re always whining. 

55
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:02,520
Mom.

56
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:03,200
What?

57
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,200
Give me some money.

58
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,000
Go take a shower.

59
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,480
But it’s cold.

60
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:13,000
Ko Song, please go home.

61
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:14,560
I’ll go now.

62
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,360
What a boy!

63
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,880
Do you miss me? 
Is that why you come here so early?

64
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,440
Can you come to a plant shop with me?

65
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,960
I can’t carry it by myself.

66
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,040
What?

67
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,480
So you just need a laborer.

68
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,600
Didn’t you tell me that if I need help, 
I can always tell our gang’s leader?

69
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:46,280
You are wicked, Ko Song.

70
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,680
I’ll give all the oranges on my tree to you.

71
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,800
Good deal. 

72
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:56,200
Give me five minutes to take a shower.

73
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,840
Argh!

74
00:05:10,440 --> 00:05:11,200
It’s so cold.

75
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,600
It’s so cold.

76
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:37,840
How are you going to carry a plant 
on a bike?

77
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:41,960
Wait here.

78
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:49,200
Tada!

79
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:51,920
I don’t think it’s a good idea.

80
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,760
Why?

81
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,800
This is my dad’s sidecar motorcycle.

82
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,680
This is our chance.

83
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,160
My dad just came back from sailing.

84
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,360
He will be sleeping until the afternoon.

85
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,680
Why do you always 
want to do dangerous things?

86
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:09,360
Are you saying no?

87
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,240
This is so fun.

88
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,320
Slow down. I’m not in a hurry.

89
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:28,160
You’re such a killjoy.

90
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,320
This is so fun.

91
00:06:42,960 --> 00:06:44,120
What are you going to buy?

92
00:06:44,880 --> 00:06:45,760
I’ll help you look for it.

93
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,520
Do you know anything about plants?

94
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:52,960
Give me 30 seconds, and I’ll find it.

95
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:56,240
My dad told me 
to buy three Mother-in-Law’s Tongue plants.

96
00:06:58,080 --> 00:06:59,760
Mother-in-Law’s Tongue?

97
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,640
Didn’t you say you could find it?

98
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:07,720
Boo!

99
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,720
Does this look like mother-in-law’s tongue?

100
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:17,520
Silly.

101
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,320
There, mother-in-law’s tongue.

102
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,240
Excuse me. 
Are these mother-in-law’s tongues?

103
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,000
Yes.

104
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,320
How many ones do you want?

105
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,640
The plants are growing well.

106
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,520
We’ll look around a bit.

107
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,080
We’ll tell you 
when we pick the ones we want.

108
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,080
Sure.

109
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:51,320
Hey.

110
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,720
We can’t just pick from what we see.

111
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:55,760
We need to feel the leaf.

112
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,680
The leaf should be firm, upright, 

113
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,240
and fleshy like this.

114
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:06,280
If the leaf is leggy or drooping, 

115
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,000
it means it doesn’t get enough sunlight.

116
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:14,520
The plant has many breeds, 
such as dwarf or hybrid.

117
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:18,720
Why?

118
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,480
Don’t you believe what I said?

119
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,600
I believe you.

120
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,800
It just feels a bit strange.

121
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:27,800
Is that a compliment or criticism?

122
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,200
Neither.

123
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,040
My mom is a plant enthusiast.

124
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,960
I help her with gardening plants in my house.

125
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,600
You know how my mom is.

126
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,120
You’re surprised, right?

127
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:46,480
Yes.

128
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:49,640
Excuse me. We will take these three.

129
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,440
Here.

130
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,080
Thank you.

131
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,720
Do you want to plant an orange tree 
in your house?

132
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,600
You seem to really like it.

133
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:18,960
I like the one planted next to my fence.

134
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,280
Let’s go. Shall we?

135
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:36,800
You need to choose 
between holding on to the plants and me.

136
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,400
Don’t forget to wear the helmet.

137
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,440
Hold tightly. Otherwise, you may fall off.

138
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,760
Did I really see it?

139
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:44,000
Why am I always the only one who sees this?

140
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,120
He could just hold on to his shoulders.

141
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,680
Are your parents home?

142
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,560
My dad is.

143
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:03,520
He’s going to plant these plants soon.

144
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,680
You should put the bike back 
before your dad finds out.

145
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:08,600
That’s right.

146
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,320
I’ve got to go.

147
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,880
My wage is one bag of oranges.

148
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,720
Okay.

149
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,000
I’ll take this.

150
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,320
That piece is mine.

151
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,800
Why didn’t you take other pieces?

152
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,680
There is no honor among thieves.

153
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,120
Hey!

154
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,960
I was eyeing that piece.

155
00:11:44,160 --> 00:11:44,960
Why did you take it?

156
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,720
This one is yours?

157
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,160
Yes, I put my name on it.

158
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,600
I wish your mouth gets burned from eating it.

159
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:58,840
August, what’s wrong with you?
Why don’t you eat it?

160
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:01,360
Normally, you like to steal other people’s food.

161
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:05,680
He’s probably thinking about 
the person who left him the note.

162
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,040
You are probably right.

163
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,320
So what happened, August?

164
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,600
Why have you been so quiet lately?

165
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,720
Are you keeping a secret from us?

166
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:15,040
No.

167
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:21,000
I’ve never kept a secret from anyone.

168
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:26,440
Don’t you guys dare keep a secret from me.

169
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,800
He’s delusional.

170
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,240
Let’s dig in.

171
00:12:30,760 --> 00:12:32,400
If August is back to his normal self, 
we won’t get to eat it.

172
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:45,440
Hey!

173
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,320
Hey!

174
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,600
Hey!

175
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:51,960
The new semester will start soon.

176
00:12:51,960 --> 00:12:52,640
Time flies so fast.

177
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,680
I don’t want to go to school yet.

178
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:58,400
I still want to wake up late. 

179
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,480
Why are you mentioning it?

180
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:02,120
You always wake up late 
even when it’s a school day.

181
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:03,960
What?

182
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:07,080
Hey!

183
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,680
Why do you keep saying ‘hey’?

184
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,360
Why did you hit me?

185
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:18,640
I don’t want the school to start.

186
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,520
Don’t you want to become an adult?

187
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:23,920
No.

188
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:28,880
I want to be with you forever.

189
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,080
Is he talking about us?

190
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:34,320
Probably not.

191
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,160
I’m talking about you guys.

192
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,480
Let’s dig in.

193
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:48,240
Here.

194
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,720
Cut it out.

195
00:13:59,160 --> 00:14:01,000
I heard that we need to join a club.

196
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:03,680
Why don’t we join the same club?

197
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:04,360
What do you think?

198
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,360
Which club should we join?

199
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,800
Let’s join the club 
that doesn’t check attendance.

200
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,720
I think we should join different clubs.

201
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:13,680
Why do you want to do that?

202
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:17,920
You want to join the basketball club, don’t you?

203
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:20,200
Yes, but…

204
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,760
I agree with Augar.

205
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,280
We have different interests, Ko Neung.

206
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,320
That’s right.

207
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:34,880
Fine. We can join different clubs.

208
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:39,560
We are seeing each other in class anyway.

209
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,520
It’s not a big deal to be separated for two hours.

210
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:46,480
Don’t worry, Ko.

211
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,560
I’m not worried.

212
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:50,120
I’m chill about it.

213
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:54,520
The teacher is here.

214
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:57,800
May I have your attention?

215
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:01,920
It’s time to choose your club.

216
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:02,960
Have you decided?

217
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,600
It’s just a club.

218
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,320
I won’t go anywhere.

219
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,200
I told you. 

220
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,160
I won’t disappear again.

221
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,520
Why aren’t we joining a club, boss?

222
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,480
I’m tired of it.

223
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:33,440
Everyone seems to have things 
they want to do.

224
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:35,920
Why are you tired of it? 
You still have me.

225
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:39,600
Augar joins the basketball club alone.

226
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,280
He will miss us, right?

227
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:47,640
He is just acting.

228
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,680
Augar, you pretend to be happy, right?

229
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:51,880
Stop it, August.

230
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:56,800
I may be the only one without goals.

231
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,520
Everyone knows what they like.

232
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,160
Look at Augar.

233
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,960
He likes sports. So he joins a sports club.

234
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,720
Ko Song and Achi like academic competitions.

235
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:05,920
So they work hard on it.

236
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:07,720
Even you, 

237
00:16:08,360 --> 00:16:09,600
who seems to have no goals like me.

238
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:14,160
But you work hard at the art and manga club. 

239
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,640
Why don’t you join a quiz show with me?

240
00:16:23,680 --> 00:16:24,520
I’m going to be serious now.

241
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,080
Listen to me.

242
00:16:27,240 --> 00:16:28,480
I’m saying this as your friend.

243
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:34,160
We all have different interests.

244
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:37,560
You shouldn’t look down on yourself like this.

245
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:44,160
Many people out there 
don’t know what they like or dislike.

246
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,920
My brother is going to turn 35 soon.

247
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:50,280
But he still plays Tamagotchi.

248
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,680
Your best friend, the porridge shop’s owner.

249
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,880
He opened the shop when he was 60.

250
00:16:56,680 --> 00:16:57,560
That’s enough, August.

251
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:58,920
You make me feel guilty.

252
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,160
You are preaching to me 
more than my dad does.

253
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:09,160
But I know what you like.

254
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:10,840
What are you talking about?

255
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:13,880
Promise me if I tell you, 
you won’t be mad at me.

256
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:16,680
I promise.

257
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:20,920
That day on the boat, 

258
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,200
what did you do with Ko Song?

259
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:25,720
See?

260
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:27,080
You’re not answering.

261
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,760
You like Ko Song, don’t you?

262
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:32,040
I saw you kiss Ko Song on the boat.

263
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,040
I’m just trying to think 
what you’re talking about. 

264
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:36,680
This is obvious.

265
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:37,920
So obvious.

266
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,120
I…

267
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,720
I knew it.

268
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:44,000
You like Ko Song, don’t you?

269
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:46,840
You are talking nonsense, August.

270
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,360
(I woke up to watch the sunrise.)

271
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,280
(I turned to look at him.)

272
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:20,160
(Then I reached 
to take the flip-flop next to him.)

273
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:24,040
That’s all.

274
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,480
Don’t tell me that you’ve been acting strange 

275
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:32,560
since we got back from the boat trip 

276
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,240
